A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing Mr. Tyler Perry and dedicating a road in his honor; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Mr. Tyler Perry was born on September 13, 1969, in New Orleans, Louisiana;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, in 1998, his first musical, I Know I've Been Changed, premiered at the famous
5 Fox Theatre in Atlanta; in 2005, his first feature film, Diary Of A Mad Black Woman,
6 debuted at number one; and in 2006, he released his first book, Don't Make A Black Woman
7 Take Off Her Earrings: Madea's Uninhibited Commentaries On Life And Love, which
8 remained on the New York Times bestseller list for eight weeks; and
9 WHEREAS, in 2007, Mr. Perry's comedic talents delighted audiences worldwide with the
10 TBS series House of Payne and later with the series Meet the Browns, which were the highest
11 and second highest rated first-run syndicated cable shows of all time, respectively, and he
12 currently has four television series on Oprah Winfrey's network, OWN; and
13 WHEREAS, in 2008, he revitalized Delta Airlines' former headquarters and opened a
14 200,000 square foot studio in Atlanta that employs hundreds of Georgians, and in 2015, Mr.
15 Perry bought 330 acres of the former military base, Fort McPherson, on which he will restore
